modules.description: Provides functions to format and colorize strings using ANSI escape codes. Works with strings and character sequences to apply foreground and background colors, as well as text styles. Used to enhance terminal output with visual distinctions, such as highlighting errors or success messages.

Provides functions to create and combine terminal color and style attributes, and applies them to strings for colored output. Works with custom types for colors and attributes, including foreground and background options. Used to format console logs, terminal interfaces, and text-based user interactions with specific visual styles.
